8 An Act relating to home service contracts; creating
the Oklahoma Home Service Act; providing short title;
9 requiring certain company to make certain information
visible in certain locations; requiring certain
10 personnel to maintain certain requirements; requiring
certain persons performing certain work to be in good
11 standing; requiring certain company to provide
certain information to certain policyholder within
12 certain time period; requiring certain company to
arrange certain assessment within certain time
13 period; providing for codification; and providing an
effective date.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 7600 of Title 36, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. This act shall be known and may be cited as the "Oklahoma
21 Home Service Act".
22 B. Home warranty companies shall make visible in their
23 principal place of business and official company website, if
24 applicable, by posting in a conspicuous location the following:
SENATE FLOOR VERSION - HB4139 SFLR Page 1
(Bold face denotes Committee Amendments)

1 1. All applicable fees; and
2 2. Detailed pricing for covered modifications, including labor
3 and parts.
4 C. Any employed or contracted repair personnel of a home
5 warranty company shall:
6 1. Be bonded and insured;
7 2. Hold a valid state license; or
8 3. Present documented proof of required training or
9 certifications.
10 D. Any employed or contracted repair personnl of a home
11 warranty company performing work regulated by Oklahoma professional
12 and occupational licensing and registration laws shall comply with
13 all Oklahoma state licensing and registration laws, including
14 holding a current license or registration in good standing.
15 E. Home warranty companies shall provide all specific licenses,
16 training standards, or certifications required of hired contractors
17 and employees to the policyholder within twenty-four (24) hours upon
18 request.
19 F. Home warranty companies shall arrange the appropriate
20 representative to assess any covered warranty item no later than
21 forty-eight (48) hours after a claim is submitted.
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
23 COMMITTEE REPORT BY: COMMITTEE ON BUSINESS AND INSURANCE
